 into pieces (approx. 3 cm)","3 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","2 cm piece fresh turmeric, peeled (see Tips)","2 tbsp psyllium husks","150 g pure maple syrup","1 tbsp ground cinnamon","¼ tsp ground cardamom","¼ tsp salt","100 g sultanas"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["2 tbsp coconut oil","1 tbsp plant-based milk of choice","60 g orange juice","1 pinch salt"]}],"id":"r341829","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-wY0juSXNkSg\/XZWdDya6SLI\/AAAAAAAAeiw\/hCn3Gy9zHggDMykbFV4GYNz1bm7Znk6CACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_CJHIHTo_hFK-fnNW.png","title":"Raw pineapple and turmeric cake","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.1 g","fat":"25.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"23.3 g","calories":"1514.7 kJ \/ 360.6 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, bowl, slice tin (18 x 22 cm), refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["If you don't have time to soak\/activate your nuts and dates, soak them in boiling water for 30 minutes, then drain and use as directed.","Small and crunchy, hemp seeds are derived from the hemp plant. They contain all the amino acids (proteins) essential for the body and also are high in omega-3 and omega-6. These seeds can be great for reducing joint pain, improving gut health and reducing sugar cravings. You can find them at some major supermarkets, health food stores and online.","You can replace the fresh turmeric with ½ teaspoon of ground turmeric in this recipe.","<strong>Orange powder:<\/strong> Preheat oven to 60°C. Place peel of 6 oranges (cut into 4 cm long strips, no white pith) onto a lined baking tray and dehydrate for 3-4 hours (60°C), until peel is dry and crisp. Place peel into mixing bowl and mill <strong>2 min\/speed 10<\/strong> or to fine powder. Use as desired or store in a sealable container in the pantry for up to 1 month."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","5h 20m","12 portions"]}